        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer790234323" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13882763887624321501">THE SECRET OF THE OLD CLOCK by Carolyn Keene (Pen Name) is the first book of the Nancy Drew series. The story is &quot;wholesomely&quot; exciting, and the Nancy Drew character is a great role model for all young girls. She is a smart, compassionate super sleuth, and I enjoyed re-reading my very first mystery story. In later books, Nancy gains a boyfriend, Ned Nickerson, and along with the help of her good friends, cousins Bess and George, Nancy solves many mysteries. <br/><br/>I am preparing a library presentation,</span>
  <span id="freeText13882763887624321501" style="display:none">THE SECRET OF THE OLD CLOCK by Carolyn Keene (Pen Name) is the first book of the Nancy Drew series. The story is "wholesomely" exciting, and the Nancy Drew character is a great role model for all young girls. She is a smart, compassionate super sleuth, and I enjoyed re-reading my very first mystery story. In later books, Nancy gains a boyfriend, Ned Nickerson, and along with the help of her good friends, cousins Bess and George, Nancy solves many mysteries. <br /><br />I am preparing a library presentation, which includes how I came to write my debut mystery-thriller, DEAD LOVE. The second in the series, DEAD PROMISE, quickly followed. I realized the first mystery that I read was The Secret of the Old Clock. My interest in mysteries and romance thrillers continues.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13882763887624321501" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
