<span id="freeTextContainer10656094240876215324">I think Nancy drew was the beginning of the end for me. Her adventures and the mysteries that she solved made me yearn to solve my own. This made me inquisitive, leading to a job as a journalist at 14. It also made me want to write. <br/><br/>And here I am...just a few years later (Ok, more than a few), and I&apos;m a writer of suspense, mysteries and thrillers! :) Go figure.<br/><br/>I recommend this book for pre-teens and young teens. It&apos;s a great escape. And for women who want to remember a piece of their youth, pick</span>
  <span id="freeText10656094240876215324" style="display:none">I think Nancy drew was the beginning of the end for me. Her adventures and the mysteries that she solved made me yearn to solve my own. This made me inquisitive, leading to a job as a journalist at 14. It also made me want to write. <br /><br />And here I am...just a few years later (Ok, more than a few), and I'm a writer of suspense, mysteries and thrillers! :) Go figure.<br /><br />I recommend this book for pre-teens and young teens. It's a great escape. And for women who want to remember a piece of their youth, pick it up and read it now. :)<br /><br />Cheryl Kaye Tardif</span>
