        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1726022858" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5546426269915541639">The very first Nancy Drew—this one has Nancy investigating and uncovering the secret of a lost will and in the process helping a number of deserving people. I love how sweet and charming the original series of books is (something I seem to always say—and which the newer series seem to lack). And this one has Nancy solving pretty much the entire mystery on her own (with a bit of her father’s help)—Bess, George, and Ned hadn’t appeared on the scene yet, there was only her friend Helen Corning who </span>
  <span id="freeText5546426269915541639" style="display:none">The very first Nancy Drew—this one has Nancy investigating and uncovering the secret of a lost will and in the process helping a number of deserving people. I love how sweet and charming the original series of books is (something I seem to always say—and which the newer series seem to lack). And this one has Nancy solving pretty much the entire mystery on her own (with a bit of her father’s help)—Bess, George, and Ned hadn’t appeared on the scene yet, there was only her friend Helen Corning who doesn’t really have much of a role in the investigation itself. Great fun!</span>
  <a data-text-id="5546426269915541639" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


